<br>
First of all, hi to the people who are compelled to post a &quot;Hi Sedar!&quot;. I can read your essential thoughts, and interpret your very soul (read: neuro transmissions), even before you can tell!! Eerie huh? Yes,  'Psychology Graduate Students' have that tendency. Anyways, back on track, here me out...<br>
<br>
[[INQUIRE:]<br>
I have an inquire: How many people feel they are in a situation of being controlled, or bound by fear of retribution and insult? Everquest related of course; more specific-by a guild...<br>
<br>
-Have you ever been afraid of being kicked out of a guild because of saying something that should have, naturally, been said? &quot;So and So, is soo rude and rediculously unfair to people, and it's so obvious! Why do people put up with it.&quot; or &quot;Lay off of him/her/them.&quot;<br>
<br>
-Have you ever been in a predicament where you should have stood up to guild leadership, in order to protect the rights and decency of an individual (backed up a fellow guildmate-doing what was right)? &quot;Gawd, I should say something, but I will get the short end of the stick; officers are already on the prowl.&quot;<br>
<br>
-While guilded or raiding, have you ever been subjected to violation of, if in a real world scenario, civil rights? (Harrased, abused, biased) Think about it, this should not be an easy question to answer.<br>
<br>
-This is a simple one: have you ever felt like a flea amongst fleas on a dog, while in a guild? Take that literal as well. (non-literal for instance: your voice, opinion, feelings are not taken into account whatsoever)<br>
<br>
-Have you felt your leadership/officership is incompetent for a good portion of his/her duration? Have you felt his/her leadership values have gone down the toilet over time, but are affraid to say something?<br>
<br>
-Have you felt your leadership/officership could have handled 'many' situations better than they were actually handled? Have you felt there was no way, shape, or form, that you would tell them this?<br>
<br>
These are some simple question to think about. Obviously, people will not post here, for fear of retribution, ironically. I think this is a good thread to keep the info consciously actively, and working. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Now, do some of these things happen in normal situations of life? Yes. Does that give the infraction validity, or justification? No. Any one violation of these( I might add I prudently picked these questions)questions are grounds for a 'red flag'. I can go on about the &quot;red flag&quot;, but choose not to, at this time. Basically think of this, yeah someone makes racial slurs in the 'real life', but is it right? And will it fly with society? Is it the norm to continue to do so? Think along those lines, and you'll get the drift. For the record, I hate racial slurs. I believe 'order' is necessary. <br>
<br>
Ah, to address the skeptics. I have no ill intentions, or primary motives towards any one group, guild, organization, or person. I just have noticed some interesting mishaps among various servers, if you will, that really beg a few questions. I won't list the questions in this curiousity post. However, please do feel free to answer or comment on any part of this, unorganized and not to MLA/PLA format, insight.<br>
<br>
[A bit of a 'deep rant':]<br>
<br>
I think it is safe to say, EQ is indeed &quot;life&quot; for some people; yeah, so, who cares...whatever floats your boat. I certainly think EQ is a great escape, and a fun one at that. EQ can mean 'alot' to people-consequently their lives; so being in a fantasy world, should they endure the same real life garbage? Should they still put up with utter and total Bulls---? How about, should they have to? I think the EQ world has adopted many societal, political, socioeconomic models, yet is it safe to say there is organization and happiness within these created models? For the most part, no! Moreover, I have heard lots of paradox's, oxymorons, whatever you want to call them, but one that stands out is, &quot;Get a life, just because I don't play 24/7... yada yada yada...&quot;. Now to rant a little deeper, cut the crap, if you play EQ- you are in the same damn cloud as anyone else. There is no ifs, ands or buts about it. By saying the aforementioned quote, you essentially create a logical fallacy of a 'red herring' for yourself; you evade the real issue, or picture. <br>
<br>
SO with that all said and done, we know that EQ can be life to many people, we know that everyone is in the same cloud/boat (depending on your level of achievement), and we know that there is quite possibly violations happening, of real life peoples dignities.<br>
<br>
With that all mentioned, why do we play?<br>
