<br>
[q]I have an inquire: How many people feel they are in a situation of being controlled, or bound by fear of retribution and insult? Everquest related of course; more specific-by a guild...[/q]<br>
<br>
I have had this situation when I was in a guild. I didn't agree with some decisions but didn't say anything because I was new to the game and figured I didn't know enough about such topics to offer argument. So, it was just safer to be quiet.<br>
<br>
[q] -Have you ever been afraid of being kicked out of a guild because of saying something that should have, naturally, been said? &quot;So and So, is soo rude and rediculously unfair to people, and it's so obvious! Why do people put up with it.&quot; or &quot;Lay off of him/her/them.&quot; [/q]<br>
<br>
Sticking up for people is sort of noble. I enjoy defending someone if I feel they are right. As I grew in the game and realized that guilds were expendable, (meaning if one guild lets you go, theres always another one right there to scoop you up) I was not afraid to say what I felt. <br>
<br>
[q] -Have you ever been in a predicament where you should have stood up to guild leadership, in order to protect the rights and decency of an individual (backed up a fellow guildmate-doing what was right)? &quot;Gawd, I should say something, but I will get the short end of the stick; officers are already on the prowl.&quot; [/q]<br>
<br>
I was a guildmaster that decided to take a break from leading. I joined another guild. This guild knew I was a guildmaster. When I saw people getting stepped on and officers/guildmasters ruling with an iron fist, I stood up to people and offered my words as theirs for them. I was quickly told to sit down and shut up. I may have been a guildmaster in my old guild but here, I am just a nobody like everyone else..   after some explatives, i detagged...<br>
<br>
[q] -While guilded or raiding, have you ever been subjected to violation of, if in a real world scenario, civil rights? (Harrased, abused, biased) Think about it, this should not be an easy question to answer. [/q]<br>
<br>
Harassed, abused, yup. I had issues where people actually got my number, called my home and complained about something posted on an ezboard. Even went as far as threatening personal injury. Good thing I record my phone conversations =D<br>
<br>
[q] -This is a simple one: have you ever felt like a flea amongst fleas on a dog, while in a guild? Take that literal as well. (non-literal for instance: your voice, opinion, feelings are not taken into account whatsoever) [/q]<br>
<br>
Yup. Was in the guild that I told u about earlier that I detagged myself. Too many members in a guild means you all become slaves to tyranny since there is no other way to lead people in EQ otherwise.<br>
<br>
[q] -Have you felt your leadership/officership is incompetent for a good portion of his/her duration? Have you felt his/her leadership values have gone down the toilet over time, but are affraid to say something? [/q]<br>
<br>
I can answer this question in several ways:<br>
Officership being incompetent. As guildmaster, I have had plenty of incompetent officers for a good portion of their duration.  I have had  several &quot;leaders&quot; create their own guilds off of mine, and apparently their leadership has gone down the toilet over time since they no longer lead their guilds. (and yes, I am still guildmaster of my guild).<br>
<br>
I can also answer this from my ex guildies point of view regarding my leadership. Many have felt the same way about me. But only officers and guildmasters will have the ability to tell you that leading a guild is a pain in the ass. You make rules. Everyone agrees to them, and when they break them, and you enforce them, you are an @#%$. You be nice to people, either by power leveling them, giving them free gear, upgrading them, helping them with their quests, etc.  and then they just up and leave your guild someday. After this gets repeatedly done to a guildmaster/officer, their nice streak fades...  This is where I am at. I am not as giving/caring as I once was, cuz there is no point or need. No matter how hard you try, its all useless. Honor, respect, trust and other chivalrous codes are almost non-existant in many players. Greed and self gain is all that many people strive for. Its apparently the only things that pay off...<br>
<br>
[q] -Have you felt your leadership/officership could have handled 'many' situations better than they were actually handled? Have you felt there was no way, shape, or form, that you would tell them this? [/q]<br>
<br>
Dur.... if someone knew the correct answer at the time, naturally they would do it the right way. You make decisions based on all the knowledge at hand. Your decision is going to make some happy and some not. You cant please everyone all the time. So regardless of what decision an officer/guildmaster makes, someone hates it!<br>
<br>
As far as telling officers/guildmasters of your disapproval... it basically is, majority rules. Its like america voting for the next political leader; x amount votes for this guy,  x amount votes for the other one.  no matter which one wins, someones going to be unhappy about that decision. but the best you can do is please as many as possible, and hope the ones you dont please, you can find a way to make them happy later and hope they respect your decisions in the meantime.<br>
<br>
They can tell us all they want, but what can we do, really?<br>
<br>
Anyway, there is your answer from me. Probably going to be your only serious one. Watch.<br>
